wall of the fourth circle, and they regained the main street climbing up to\par
the Citadel. Step by step they went, while Merry swayed and murmured as one in\par
sleep.\par
'I'll never get him there,' thought Pippin. 'Is there no one to help me?\par
I can't leave him here.' Just then to his surprise a boy came running up\par
behind, and as he passed he recognized Bergil Beregond's son.\par
'Hullo, Bergil!' he called. 'Where are you going? Glad to see you again,\par
