unsheathed sword, and at his feet his shield, The light of the torches\par
shimmered in his white hair like sun in the spray of a fountain, but his face\par
was fair and young, save that a peace lay on it beyond the reach of youth; and\par
it seemed that he slept.\par
When they had stood silent for a time beside the king, Imrahil said:\par
'Where is the Steward? And where also is Mithrandir?'\par
And one of the guards answered: 'The Steward of Gondor is in the Houses\par
of Healing.'\par
But \'c9omer said: 'Where is the Lady \'c9owyn, my sister; for surely she\par
should be lying beside the king, and in no less honour? Where have they\par
bestowed her?'\par
And Imrahil said: 'But the Lady \'c9owyn was yet living when they bore her\par
hither. Did you not know?'\par
Then hope unlooked-for came so suddenly to \'c9omer's heart, and with it the\par
bite of care and fear renewed, that he said no more, but turned and went\par
swiftly from the hall; and the Prince followed him. And when they came forth\par
