\'c9owyn, where is she?'\par
And Gandalf answered: 'She lies within and is not dead, but is near\par
death. But the Lord Faramir was wounded by an evil dart, as you have heard,\par
and he is now the Steward; for Denethor has departed, and his house is in\par
ashes.' And they were filled with grief and wonder at the tale that he told.\par
But Imrahil said: 'So victory is shorn of gladness, and it is bitter\par
bought, if both Gondor and Rohan are in one day bereft of their lords. \'c9omer\par
rules the Rohirrim. Who shall rule the City meanwhile? Shall we not send now\par
for the Lord Aragorn?'\par
And the cloaked man spoke and said: 'He is come.' And they saw as he\par
stepped into the light of the lantern by the door that it was Aragorn, wrapped\par
in the grey cloak of L\'f3rien above his mail, and bearing no other token than\par
the green stone of Galadriel. 'I have come because Gandalf begs me to do so,'\par
