'Except Gandalf, of course. I think they must be related. My dear ass, your\par
pack is lying by your bed, and you had it on your back when I met you. He saw\par
it all the time, of course. And anyway I have some stuff of my own. Come on\par
now! Longbottom Leaf it is. Fill up while I run and see about some food. And\par
then let's be easy for a bit. Dear me! We Tooks and Brandybucks, we can't live\par
long on the heights.'\par
'No,' said Merry. 'I can't. Not yet, at any rate. But at least, Pippin,\par
we can now see them, and honour them. It is best to love first what you are\par
fitted to love, I suppose: you must start somewhere and have some roots, and\par
the soil of the Shire is deep. Still there are things deeper and higher; and\par
not a gaffer could tend his garden in what he calls peace but for them,\par
