prowled all about them, and they heard the howling of wolves. The wind had\par
died and all the air seemed still. They could see little, for though it was\par
cloudless and the waxing moon was four nights old, there were smokes and fumes\par
that rose out of the earth and the white crescent was shrouded in the mists of\par
