steed, and with his company galloped madly back to Cirith Gorgor. But as they\par
went his soldiers blew their horns in signal long arranged; and even before\par
they came to the gate Sauron sprang his trap.\par
Drums rolled and fires leaped up. The great doors of the Black Gate swung\par
back wide. Out of it streamed a great host as swiftly as swirling waters when\par
a sluice is lifted.\par
The Captains mounted again and rode back, and from the host of Mordor\par
there went up a jeering yell. Dust rose smothering the air, as from nearby\par
there marched up an army of Easterlings that had waited for the signal in the\par
shadows of Ered Lithui beyond the further Tower. Down from the hills on either\par
side of the Morannon poured Orcs innumerable. The men of the West were\par
trapped, and soon. all about the grey mounds where they stood, forces ten\par
times and more than ten times their match would ring them in a sea of enemies.\par
