me, Mr. Frodo, but I didn't know as anything grew in Mordor! But if I had\par
a'known, this is just what I'd have looked for. These thorns must be a foot\par
long by the feel of them; they've stuck through everything I've got on. Wish\par
I'd a'put that mail-shirt on!'\par
'Orc-mail doesn't keep these thorns out,' said Frodo. 'Not even a leather\par
jerkin is any good.'\par
They had a struggle to get out of the thicket. The thorns and briars were\par
