stones and boulders lying thick at the bottom of the great ravine. But\par
presently he stopped again.\par
'It's no good, Sam,' he said. 'I can't manage it. This mail-shirt, I\par
mean. Not in my present state. Even my mithril-coat seemed heavy when I was\par
