I could. Let it go then!'\par
Frodo laid aside his cloak and took off the orc-mail and flung it away.\par
He shivered a little. 'What I really need is something warm,' he said. 'It's\par
gone cold, or else I've caught a chill.'\par
'You can have my cloak, Mr. Frodo,' said Sam. He unslung his pack and\par
took out the elven-cloak. 'How's this, Mr. Frodo?' he said. 'You wrap that\par
orc-rag close round you, and put the belt outside it. Then this can go over\par
all. It don't look quite orc-fashion, but it'll keep you warmer; and I daresay\par
