Frodo took the cloak and fastened the brooch. 'That's better!' he said.\par
'I feel much lighter. I can go on now. But this blind dark seems to be getting\par
into my heart. As I lay in prison, Sam. I tried to remember the Brandywine,\par
and Woody End, and The Water running through the mill at Hobbiton. But I can't\par
see them now.'\par
'There now, Mr. Frodo, it's you that's talking of water this time!' said\par
Sam. 'If only the Lady could see us or hear us, I'd say to her: Your Ladyship,\par
