speak for some time. Then Frodo breathed a sigh of relief. 'It's passed,' he\par
said. They stood up, and then they both stared in wonder. Away to their left,\par
southward, against a sky that was turning grey, the peaks and high ridges of\par
the great range began to appear dark and black, visible shapes. Light was\par
growing behind them. Slowly it crept towards the North. There was battle far\par
above in the high spaces of the air. The billowing clouds of Mordor were being\par
driven back, their edges tattering as a wind out of the living world came up\par
