between the mountains. It sloped up gently northward, and at its bottom went\par
the bed of a now dry and withered stream. Beyond its stony course they saw a\par
beaten path that wound its way under the feet of the westward cliffs. Had they\par
known, they could have reached it quicker, for it was a track that left the\par
main Morgul-road at the western bridge-end and went down by a long stair cut\par
in the rock to the valley's bottom. It was used by patrols or by messengers\par
