overhung, and they could not be seen from above; but the path made many bends,\par
and at each bend they gripped their sword-hilts and went forward cautiously.\par
The light grew no stronger, for Orodruin was still belching forth a great\par
fume that, beaten upwards by the opposing airs, mounted higher and higher,\par
until it reached a region above the wind and spread in an immeasurable roof,\par
whose central pillar rose out of the shadows beyond their view. They had\par
trudged for more than an hour when they heard a sound that brought them to a\par
