country crawling with enemies, even if we did get down.'\par
'Still we shall have to try,' said Frodo. 'It's no worse than I expected.\par
I never hoped to get across. I can't see any hope of it now. But I've still\par
got to do the best I can. At present that is to avoid being captured as long\par
as possible. So we must still go northwards, I think, and see what it is like\par
where the open plain is narrower.'\par
'I guess what it'll be like,' said Sam. 'Where it's narrower the Orcs and\par
Men will just be packed closer. You'll see, Mr. Frodo.'\par
'I dare say I shall, if we ever get so far,' said Frodo and turned away.\par
They soon found that it was impossible to make their way along the crest\par
