'It saved his life anyhow,' said the soldier. 'Why, before I knew he was\par
wanted I shot him, as neat as neat, at fifty paces right in the back; but he\par
ran on.'\par
'Garn! You missed him,' said the tracker. 'First you shoot wild, then you\par
run too slow, and then you send for the poor trackers. I've had enough of\par
you.' He loped off.\par
'You come back,' shouted the soldier, 'or I'll report you!'\par
'Who to? Not to your precious Shagrat. He won't be captain any more.'\par
'I'll give your name and number to the Nazg\'fbl,' said the soldier lowering\par
his voice to a hiss. 'One of _them_'s in charge at the Tower now.'\par
The other halted, and his voice was full of fear and rage. 'You cursed\par
peaching sneakthief!' he yelled. 'You can't do your job, and you can't even\par
