flesh off you! If the enemy doesn't get them first. They've done in Number\par
One, I've heard, and I hope it's true!'\par
The big orc, spear in hand, leapt after him. But the tracker, springing\par
behind a stone, put an arrow in his eye as he ran up, and he fell with a\par
