'We know it well,' said Aragorn, 'and never shall it be forgotten in\par
Minas Tirith or in Edoras.'\par
'_Never_ is too long a word even for me,' said Treebeard. 'Not while your\par
kingdoms last, you mean; but they will have to last long indeed to seem long\par
to Ents.'\par
'The New Age begins,' said Gandalf, 'and in this age it may well prove\par
that the kingdoms of Men shall outlast you, Fangorn my friend. But now come\par
