Orthanc yet? For I do not suppose that he will think you have improved the\par
view from his windows.'\par
Treebeard gave Gandalf a long look, a most cunning look, Merry thought.\par
'Ah!' he said. 'I thought you would come to that. Weary of Orthanc? Very weary\par
at last; but not so weary of his tower as he was weary of my voice. _Hoom_! I\par
gave him some long tales, or at least what might be thought long in your\par
speech.'\par
'Then why did he stay to listen? Did you go into Orthanc?' asked Gandalf.\par
_'Hoom_, no, not into Orthanc!' said Treebeard. 'But he came to his\par
window and listened, because he could not get news in any other way, and\par
though he hated the news, he was greedy to have it; and I saw that he heard it\par
