_Chapter 8_\par
The Scouring of the Shire\par
It was after nightfall when, wet and tired, the travellers came at last\par
to the Brandywine, and they found the way barred. At either end of the Bridge\par
there was a great spiked gate; and on the further side of the river they could\par
see that some new houses had been built: two-storeyed with narrow straightsided\par
windows, bare and dimly lit, all very gloomy and un-Shirelike.\par
