'All right!' said Merry. 'But we shall be having a visit from the\par
Hobbiton gang any time now, I think. They won't come just to talk things over.\par
We'll try to deal with them neatly, but we must be prepared for the worst. Now\par
I've got a plan.'\par
'Very good,' said Frodo. 'You make the arrangements.'\par
Just then some hobbits, who had been sent out towards Hobbiton, came\par
running in. 'They're coming!' they said. 'A score or more. But two have gone\par
off west across country.'\par
'To Waymeet, that'll be,' said Cotton, 'to fetch more of the gang. Well,\par
it's fifteen mile each way. We needn't trouble about them just yet.'\par
Merry hurried off to give orders. Farmer Cotton cleared the street,\par
sending everyone indoors, except the older hobbits who had weapons of some\par
sort. They had not long to wait. Soon they could hear loud voices, and then\par
the tramping of heavy feet. Presently a whole squad of the ruffians came down\par
the road. They saw the barrier and laughed. They did not imagine that there\par
